THIS IS GOING TO BE CONTROVERSIAL, but you need conflict to…

SHARE | SAVE

…succeed, hear me out. Healthy conflict occurs within a diverse team. To succeed in achieving the ‘unimaginable’ you need to use that conflict to constructively destroy “group think”. Group think is when people prioritize harmony over collegial challenging and critical thinking. However, being challenged will open up your aperture to achieve your potential!!

My three secret ways working with an accountability partner in a team can propel you to unimaginable heights in your fitness goals and life, while banishing doubt:
* 	Collective Strength: A team multiplies your collective willpower. When doubt creeps in, your teammates offer unwavering support and encouragement, helping you overcome any obstacle.
* 	Shared Knowledge: Teams bring diverse expertise to the table. You can tap into a wealth of knowledge, strategies, and insights that might not be accessible on your own.
* 	Accountability Amplified: With multiple accountability partners, there’s no room for slacking. The commitment to your team ensures you stay on track and achieve your goals consistently.
Embrace the power of a supportive team with diverse thinking to shatter your limits and conquer the unimaginable!

STEAL MY SUCCES STRATEGY…

SAVE | SHARE

…by developing a driven mindset. 

Embrace the Drive for Continuous Improvement! Embrace Collaboration!!

Driven individuals never stop because they believe they can always do better. Here’s why this mindset thrives:
* 	Unleash Full Potential: Embracing the idea that you can do better means you’re continuously unlocking your full potential, pushing past limits you once thought were fixed.
* 	Adapt and Overcome: A commitment to improvement makes you resilient. Challenges become stepping stones to success, not roadblocks.
* 	Stay Motivated: The pursuit of better fuels perpetual motivation. It drives you to set and achieve new goals, spurring progress in both fitness and life.
Ready to adopt this mindset and enhance your journey? Embrace collaboration:
* 	Team Up: Partner with like-minded individuals. The exchange of ideas and support from a community enhances your journey’s depth and impact.
* 	Mentorship: Seek guidance from those who have treaded similar paths. Their experience can fast-track your growth and offer valuable insights.
* 	Network: Connect with people from various backgrounds. Diverse perspectives fuel innovation and provide fresh approaches to your goals.
Combine the power of continuous improvement and collaboration to drive success in your fitness journey and life! #ContinuousImprovement #Collaboration #SuccessMindset #onlinecoach #fitnesscoach #6pack #75HARD

DON’T MAKE THIS BEGINNER MISTAKE…

SHARE | SAVE

…of thinking you will always perform at your best. Be realistic and focus on giving your best effort!

Location: @johnreedfitness_us West Hollywood 

Sometimes you just need Quality Effort Over High Performance: The Key to Success! 

Consistency in your fitness journey and life isn’t always about high-performance days. Here’s why consistent, quality effort is the real game-changer:
* Sustainable Growth: Quality effort is something you can maintain long-term. High performance can lead to burnout.
* Building Habits: Consistently giving your best effort forms lasting habits that drive success. High performance can be sporadic.
* Continuous Progress: Quality effort, day in and day out, leads to continuous progress, which is the secret to long-term success.

Ready to make quality effort your daily routine? 
MY five ways to actively integrate it into your life:
* 	Set Realistic Goals: Define achievable, quality-focused goals that encourage steady progress.
* 	Create a Consistent Schedule: Establish a routine that ensures you consistently allocate time and energy to your fitness journey.
* 	Prioritize Active Recovery: ‘maybe I’m not ready to sprint today, but I’ll jog this hill’. Cross-training is progress. 
* 	Stay Educated: Continuously learn about fitness, nutrition, and mindset to refine your approach.
* 	Track Progress: Keep a fitness journal to monitor your consistent, quality efforts and celebrate milestones.
Consistency doesn’t always mean high performance; it means giving your best, day after day. Embrace the power of quality effort, and success will follow!  #QualityEffort #SuccessMindset #ConsistencyIsKey #onlinecoach #fitnesscoach ##6pack #75HARD
